.START 

Financo Inc. has been appointed by L.J. Hooker Corp. to act as its financial adviser in the planned sale of B. Altman & Co. 

According to Gilbert Harrison, chairman of Financo, his company is currently reviewing a number of inquiries from potential buyers.
Last week Sanford Sigoloff, chief executive officer of L.J. Hooker, announced his intention to sell the seven-unit department store chain. 

"Because of the cash needed to fund B. Altman & Co., it is L.J. Hooker's intention to complete a transaction as quickly as possible," said Mr. Harrison. 

Mr. Harrison represented L.J. Hooker in its recently completed negotiations to sell the Parisian department store chain back to Parisian's management.
He also served as L.J. Hooker's financial adviser when it acquired Bonwit Teller in 

L.J. Hooker, which is under protection from creditors under Chapter 11 of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code, also operates various shopping malls in this country and owns additional commercial real estate.
Its parent company, Hooker Corp. of Sydney, Australia, is currently being managed by a court-appointed provisional liquidator. 

